- Killing Three Birds with One Stone]

28
00:02:28,380 --> 00:02:30,340
[Hospitalization records]

29
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:31,570
Patients, Ding Dashan and Ding Dahai.

30
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:32,370
They're brothers.

31
00:02:32,510 --> 00:02:33,330
There was a fire in their home.

32
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:34,470
Ding Dashan, the elder brother,

33
00:02:34,510 --> 00:02:35,630
suffered extensive burns

34
00:02:35,790 --> 00:02:36,840
and fluid loss.

35
00:02:36,950 --> 00:02:38,370
Now, venous access
cannot be established.

36
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:39,030
He can't be given fluids.

37
00:02:39,350 --> 00:02:40,350
The problem of venous access

38
00:02:41,190 --> 00:02:42,210
can be solved with intervention,

39
00:02:42,470 --> 00:02:43,990
but for the extensive burns on his body,

40
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:44,720
he has

41
00:02:44,790 --> 00:02:45,510
no autograft skin.

42
00:02:45,750 --> 00:02:46,840
How about considering
asking his relatives to donate?

43
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,280
Both of his parents are dead,

44
00:02:48,470 --> 00:02:49,600
and he no longer has any family.

45
00:02:49,630 --> 00:02:50,580
Ding Dashan just got married.

46
00:02:50,580 --> 00:02:51,960
His wife is about to have a baby.

47
00:02:52,320 --> 00:02:53,620
If his relatives can't donate,

48
00:02:53,950 --> 00:02:55,400
the cost of subsequent skin grafts
will be expensive

49
00:02:55,750 --> 00:02:56,740
and the recovery process

50
00:02:56,750 --> 00:02:57,520
will be complicated.

51
00:02:57,750 --> 00:02:58,400
He's at risk of infection

52
00:02:58,470 --> 00:02:59,600
and multiple complications.

53
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:01,840
[Hospitalization records]

54
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:02,650
As for the younger brother,

55
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:03,800
the rest of Ding Dahai's body is fine,

56
00:03:03,950 --> 00:03:04,840
but images show

57
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:06,120
that both of his kidneys are injured.

58
00:03:07,910 --> 00:03:08,490
Both kidneys?

59
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:09,120
Both kidneys.

60
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:19,240
Mr. Wang, what do you think?

61
00:03:20,950 --> 00:03:21,730
The images show

62
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:23,240
that both kidneys are severely damaged.

63
00:03:23,910 --> 00:03:25,000
As for the extent of the damage,

64
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:26,450
we need surgery to confirm.

65
00:03:29,030 --> 00:03:30,120
Then let's go straight to the surgery.

66
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:30,730
Do it together.

67
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:33,240
Make a large incision for examination.

68
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:34,400
Su Yun.

69
00:03:34,750 --> 00:03:35,650
Notify the patient's family

70
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:36,450
that we're preparing

71
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:37,560
for surgery.

72
00:03:37,720 --> 00:03:38,610
- Okay.
- Got it.

73
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,650
The patient's left kidney
has been removed,

74
00:03:59,950 --> 00:04:01,800
and the right one
is also in a bad state.

75
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:03,170
What's his urine output?

76
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:04,890
No urine.

77
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:06,240
There's no fluid in the urethra.

78
00:04:12,440 --> 00:04:12,930
Mr. Lin.

79
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:13,970
We've tried our best.

80
00:04:14,350 --> 00:04:15,410
I can't sew it up.

81
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,200
If we do

82
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:18,050
the kidney transplant now,

83
00:04:18,070 --> 00:04:18,640
it might not be too late.

84
00:04:19,750 --> 00:04:20,320
But how can we find

85
00:04:20,390 --> 00:04:21,680
a new kidney at this moment?

86
00:04:21,950 --> 00:04:22,720
Even if we could,

87
00:04:22,880 --> 00:04:24,200
the matching time would be a problem.

88
00:04:24,270 --> 00:04:25,200
It's still too late.

89
00:04:36,190 --> 00:04:36,800
Mr. Wang.

90
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,490
This kid is only 26 years old.

91
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:40,640
He's still young.

92
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:42,240
Do something.

93
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:54,460
[Emergency]

94
00:05:11,710 --> 00:05:12,610
I'm done

95
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:13,530
and waiting for a kidney transplant.

96
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:14,730
What's your situation?

97
00:05:18,190 --> 00:05:19,170
He can't keep his right kidney either?

98
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:22,440
Mr. Lin just called
for a kidney transplant,

99
00:05:22,830 --> 00:05:24,090
which costs over 100,000.

100
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:26,090
Their house just caught fire.

101
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:27,200
And his baby is on the way.

102
00:05:27,710 --> 00:05:28,370
So sorry for that.

103
00:05:43,260 --> 00:05:46,660
[Hospitalization records]

104
00:05:46,660 --> 00:05:47,580
[Ding Dashan, Hospitalization records]

105
00:05:47,580 --> 00:05:48,580
[Ding Dahai, Hospitalization records]

106
00:05:50,420 --> 00:05:51,900
[Ding Dahai: Both kidneys injured,
Ding Dashan: Severe burns]

107
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:54,860
[Ding Dahai: Both kidneys injured,
Ding Dashan: Severe burns]

108
00:05:54,860 --> 00:05:56,700
[Kidney transplant, Skin grafts]

109
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:02,970
They're twins.

110
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:04,440
Yes.

111
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:06,290
They're identical twins.

112
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:13,640
Hi.

113
00:06:13,710 --> 00:06:14,170
Come on.

114
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:16,790
We've come up with a new program.

115
00:06:16,880 --> 00:06:17,530
Listen to this.

116
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:18,820
Roughly,

117
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:20,090
the elder brother
gives the younger a kidney

118
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:21,000
to save his life

119
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:22,440
while the younger
gives the elder a skin graft.

120
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:23,510
The two

121
00:06:23,510 --> 00:06:24,930
give each other skin flaps and kidneys.

122
00:06:25,150 --> 00:06:25,880
As long as there's no rejection,

123
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:26,710
the perioperative treatment

124
00:06:26,710 --> 00:06:27,680
will be less difficult

125
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:28,760
and less expensive.

126
00:06:29,950 --> 00:06:30,530
In that case,

127
00:06:30,530 --> 00:06:31,680
can both survive?

128
00:06:32,630 --> 00:06:33,640
But not all twins are perfect matches

129
00:06:33,640 --> 00:06:34,690
for their organs.

130
00:06:34,950 --> 00:06:35,720
Pre-operative matching

131
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:36,930
takes at least a day,

132
00:06:38,150 --> 00:06:38,680
but we don't

133
00:06:38,750 --> 00:06:39,410
have that time.

134
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:44,440
So...

135
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:47,800
What if they don't match?

136
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:49,880
The younger brother will die.

137
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:55,410
What about my husband?

138
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:57,240
He'll lose a kidney.

139
00:06:58,950 --> 00:06:59,930
It won't affect his normal life,

140
00:07:00,150 --> 00:07:01,050
but his immunity

141
00:07:01,390 --> 00:07:02,090
will be lowered.

142
00:07:18,710 --> 00:07:19,680
Hello, Mrs. Tian.

143
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:21,410
Can I call you back later?

144
00:07:21,410 --> 00:07:22,290
Later?

145
00:07:22,510 --> 00:07:23,490
I'm in the middle

146
00:07:23,490 --> 00:07:24,320
of a mess here.

147
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:25,680
You burned down my house

148
00:07:25,710 --> 00:07:26,640
and the downstairs.

149
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:27,510
You have to pay for it

150
00:07:27,510 --> 00:07:28,440
no matter what.

151
00:07:28,710 --> 00:07:29,510
I'm sorry.

152
00:07:29,510 --> 00:07:30,610
- Can sorry help us?
- I'm sorry.

153
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:31,800
Be quick.

154
00:07:31,830 --> 00:07:32,470
The neighbors downstairs

155
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:33,530
are all here.

156
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:34,880
- I...
- Listen.

157
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:36,200
It's your fault.

158
00:07:36,270 --> 00:07:37,290
You're too careless.

159
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:37,920
Don't you know

160
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:39,120
you can't charge an e-bike

161
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:39,640
in the room?

162
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:42,170
Ignore this.

163
00:07:42,390 --> 00:07:43,070
Don't let these calls

164
00:07:43,070 --> 00:07:43,970
affect you.

165
00:07:44,750 --> 00:07:45,730
What do you think of that plan?

166
00:07:50,630 --> 00:07:52,490
My parents-in-law passed away early.

167
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:56,170
My husband and his brother

168
00:07:56,830 --> 00:07:58,170
grew up together.

169
00:07:58,920 --> 00:08:00,680
Can you keep them both alive?

170
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:03,680
That's the only way
our family will survive.

171
00:08:04,950 --> 00:08:05,970
Please.

172
00:08:06,390 --> 00:08:07,760
Think of another way

173
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:09,480
to get them both out alive,

174
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:10,170
okay?

175
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:14,090
Mr. Lin.

176
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,520
Is there any way
to save the younger brother's kidney

177
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:16,930
in the urology department?

178
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:18,640
I can help with the surgery.

179
00:08:28,190 --> 00:08:29,170
Let me try.

180
00:08:40,920 --> 00:08:41,730
I will try to keep

181
00:08:41,730 --> 00:08:42,570
the patient's right kidney.

182
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:43,160
In this way,

183
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:44,100
the elder one doesn't have
to donate his kidney.

184
00:08:44,160 --> 00:08:45,570
His skin
can recover better after surgery,

185
00:08:45,870 --> 00:08:46,760
and the younger
doesn't need a transplant.

186
00:08:48,110 --> 00:08:48,880
You are...?

187
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:50,280
She's Lin Yuan.

188
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:52,120
Graduated from Harvard

189
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:53,330
and had her internship in Man'ou.

190
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:55,400
Specializes in the diagnosis,
treatment, and surgery

191
00:08:55,470 --> 00:08:57,160
of common diseases
of general surgery and urology.

192
00:09:07,190 --> 00:09:07,850
Leave it to me.

193
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,730
I'll keep them both.

194
00:09:41,230 --> 00:09:41,920
Let me do it.

195
00:10:04,400 --> 00:10:05,330
You went to all this trouble

196
00:10:05,870 --> 00:10:06,920
just to recruit this girl?

197
00:10:07,950 --> 00:10:08,520
How is she?

198
00:10:10,110 --> 00:10:12,280
Well, I need to see her performance.

199
00:10:17,870 --> 00:10:18,400
Ms. Su,

200
00:10:19,760 --> 00:10:20,690
could you come out for a moment?

201
00:10:20,950 --> 00:10:21,880
I'd like to talk to you.

202
00:10:24,870 --> 00:10:25,810
Let's talk here.

203
00:10:28,160 --> 00:10:29,090
Why did you do it?

204
00:10:31,330 --> 00:10:32,000
Dr. Lin said

205
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,450
she could
save the patient's right kidney.

206
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:38,570
What I'm asking

207
00:10:39,190 --> 00:10:40,730
is why you poached her
for Haicheng Hospital.

208
00:10:47,230 --> 00:10:48,210
For Haicheng Hospital

209
00:10:48,230 --> 00:10:49,400
to become the Man'ou of China,

210
00:10:49,990 --> 00:10:51,240
we must learn

211
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:52,280
from Man'ou's advanced philosophy.

212
00:10:52,710 --> 00:10:54,850
Dr. Lin shares my vision

213
00:10:55,190 --> 00:10:56,760
and is willing to support me
in accomplishing my dream.

214
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:58,880
She also wants to serve our country.

215
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:01,040
You should be very proud

216
00:11:01,680 --> 00:11:03,370
to have such a wonderful

217
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:07,040
and compassionate daughter,

218
00:11:08,560 --> 00:11:09,850
shouldn't you,

219
00:11:16,040 --> 00:11:16,690
Mr. Lin?

220
00:11:35,990 --> 00:11:37,000
She's a little slow.

221
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:38,040
But she's steady.

222
00:11:40,070 --> 00:11:41,490
Those are the steadiest hands
I've ever seen.

223
00:12:01,350 --> 00:12:02,210
How is that possible?

224
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:04,240
She was...

225
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:16,570
What's going on?

226
00:12:18,230 --> 00:12:18,850
She snuck out

227
00:12:18,850 --> 00:12:20,040
of your drawer

228
00:12:20,040 --> 00:12:20,850
and pulled out a lancet

229
00:12:20,850 --> 00:12:22,330
to operate on a rag doll.

230
00:12:23,250 --> 00:12:24,090
Then,

231
00:12:24,190 --> 00:12:25,490
she hurt her index finger.

232
00:12:32,950 --> 00:12:33,570
Baby.

233
00:12:35,920 --> 00:12:36,730
Dad.

234
00:12:37,710 --> 00:12:38,730
I'm so sorry.

235
00:12:39,520 --> 00:12:41,430
I didn't listen to you.

236
00:12:41,440 --> 00:12:43,330
It's okay, sweetie.

237
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:44,640
It's going to be okay.

238
00:12:46,190 --> 00:12:47,040
Dad.

239
00:12:47,710 --> 00:12:50,850
Will I be able to operate again?

240
00:12:55,950 --> 00:12:56,760
No.

241
00:12:57,590 --> 00:12:58,880
I don't allow it.

242
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:00,640
I don't allow you

243
00:13:00,680 --> 00:13:02,120
to touch the scalpel again.

244
00:13:02,640 --> 00:13:04,040
I will.

245
00:13:04,870 --> 00:13:06,370
I'm going to operate.

246
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:09,090
I'm going to be a doctor.

247
00:13:09,520 --> 00:13:12,090
Dad, I'm going to operate!

248
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:12,970
Cut it.

249
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:21,400
Cut it.

250
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:28,880
Cut it.

251
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:30,970
Done.

252
00:13:34,950 --> 00:13:36,230
She's preserved two-thirds
of his right kidney

253
00:13:36,230 --> 00:13:37,120
and adrenal glands.

254
00:13:37,760 --> 00:13:38,870
Then as long as
his serum creatinine value

255
00:13:38,870 --> 00:13:39,760
doesn't exceed 600,

256
00:13:39,990 --> 00:13:40,970
he doesn't even need dialysis.

257
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:42,240
Just medication is enough.

258
00:13:48,470 --> 00:13:49,210
Congratulations.

259
00:13:49,710 --> 00:13:50,280
Mr. Lin,

260
00:13:50,950 --> 00:13:52,280
you have a wonderful daughter.

261
00:14:23,220 --> 00:14:25,940
[Surgery Announcement Screen,
Ding***Hai: Surgery completed]

262
00:14:33,190 --> 00:14:33,960
Doctor.

263
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:35,570
The surgery was a success.

264
00:14:39,920 --> 00:14:40,400
Thank you.

265
00:14:40,990 --> 00:14:42,160
Thank you, Dr. Lin.

266
00:14:42,280 --> 00:14:43,520
I don't know what to say.

267
00:14:43,540 --> 00:14:44,280
- Thank you.
- Don't.

268
00:14:45,940 --> 00:14:46,690
Calm down.

269
00:14:46,790 --> 00:14:47,560
If you're not feeling well,

270
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:49,000
tell the OB/GYN at once.

271
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:49,920
Thank you.

272
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:51,210
Get some rest.

273
00:14:54,350 --> 00:14:54,920
Thank you.

274
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:42,450
Lin Yuan.

275
00:15:43,520 --> 00:15:44,810
You're good at study,

276
00:15:45,220 --> 00:15:47,160
but being a doctor
requires hands-on skills.

277
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:49,810
Your hands are as good

278
00:15:49,810 --> 00:15:51,040
as normal after recuperation,

279
00:15:51,160 --> 00:15:51,610
but...

280
00:15:51,670 --> 00:15:52,810
I can use a scalpel.

281
00:15:54,040 --> 00:15:55,210
But you're not destined

282
00:15:55,240 --> 00:15:56,970
to be a top surgeon

283
00:15:56,990 --> 00:15:58,280
with that kind of difference.

284
00:15:58,320 --> 00:15:59,040
I can.

285
00:16:01,010 --> 00:16:02,520
Don't be a doctor, okay?

286
00:16:02,680 --> 00:16:03,400
I will.

287
00:16:05,070 --> 00:16:06,500
If you have to be a surgeon,

288
00:16:07,190 --> 00:16:07,850
then

289
00:16:08,420 --> 00:16:09,380
beat me.

290
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:13,840
I came back to beat you.

291
00:16:14,280 --> 00:16:15,330
Mr. Lin.

292
00:16:28,590 --> 00:16:29,210
You've been up

293
00:16:29,210 --> 00:16:30,050
all night.

294
00:16:30,050 --> 00:16:30,880
Why don't you go to sleep?

295
00:16:31,110 --> 00:16:32,450
How can your body cope?

296
00:16:33,120 --> 00:16:34,120
Eat.

297
00:16:34,250 --> 00:16:35,080
Thank you, Honey.

298
00:16:36,760 --> 00:16:38,120
Isn't this Yuan's resume?

299
00:16:38,120 --> 00:16:39,540
[Lin Yuan's Profile]

300
00:16:40,430 --> 00:16:41,080
That's her.

301
00:16:44,720 --> 00:16:45,600
She's back?

302
00:16:49,950 --> 00:16:50,720
What are you doing?

303
00:16:51,310 --> 00:16:52,650
I'm going to call her.

304
00:16:52,880 --> 00:16:53,630
She's back in the country.

305
00:16:53,630 --> 00:16:54,960
Why doesn't she go home?

306
00:16:57,870 --> 00:16:58,450
She...

307
00:16:58,720 --> 00:17:00,200
She's back.

308
00:17:00,360 --> 00:17:01,690
And she's been back for a week.

309
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:04,430
But she didn't even tell you.

310
00:17:04,430 --> 00:17:06,880
It's obvious she doesn't want
to come home.

311
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:17,730
It's all your fault.

312
00:17:18,830 --> 00:17:19,680
If you'd blamed

313
00:17:20,070 --> 00:17:20,970
or interfered less

314
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:22,390
back then,

315
00:17:22,390 --> 00:17:23,530
she wouldn't be like this.

316
00:17:24,760 --> 00:17:25,970
What's the difference

317
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:27,360
between having this daughter

318
00:17:28,030 --> 00:17:28,970
and not

319
00:17:29,240 --> 00:17:30,010
having her?

320
00:17:33,480 --> 00:17:34,840
What's wrong with her studying medicine?

321
00:17:35,760 --> 00:17:36,600
What's wrong

322
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:37,530
with being a surgeon

323
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:39,570
even if it's a little bit hard,

324
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:40,250
right?

325
00:17:40,440 --> 00:17:41,360
We're a family,

326
00:17:41,390 --> 00:17:42,570
and we can take care of each other

327
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:43,920
so she doesn't have to suffer,

328
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:45,080
right?

329
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:51,810
What are you doing?

330
00:17:52,030 --> 00:17:53,640
I'll give her a call.

331
00:17:54,720 --> 00:17:55,250
Please.

332
00:18:00,100 --> 00:18:04,020
[Haicheng Hospital]

333
00:18:14,780 --> 00:18:15,770
Eat some fruit

334
00:18:15,790 --> 00:18:16,680
for vitamins

335
00:18:16,760 --> 00:18:17,640
and trace elements.

336
00:18:18,350 --> 00:18:19,840
Are you flattering me

337
00:18:20,390 --> 00:18:21,500
to offer to spy on the rival

338
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:22,520
for 500?

339
00:18:22,680 --> 00:18:23,810
Rival?

340
00:18:24,080 --> 00:18:24,810
Hua.

341
00:18:25,070 --> 00:18:26,570
Do you really think
that girl from Man'ou

342
00:18:26,680 --> 00:18:28,210
is qualified to be Zheng Ren's rival?

343
00:18:29,870 --> 00:18:30,490
You're wrong.

344
00:18:30,590 --> 00:18:31,760
I invited her here

345
00:18:31,760 --> 00:18:32,810
to be Wang's alternate.

346
00:18:33,240 --> 00:18:33,920
Do you still nurse a grievance

347
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:34,770
for those old staff?

348
00:18:35,580 --> 00:18:36,490
I don't want anyone

349
00:18:36,550 --> 00:18:37,490
to put on airs or drop the ball

350
00:18:37,560 --> 00:18:38,730
when we have operations.

351
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:40,550
I have nothing personal

352
00:18:40,550 --> 00:18:41,290
against them.

353
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:43,600
What's more,

354
00:18:45,610 --> 00:18:46,440
one of the purposes

355
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:47,570
of her coming to Haicheng Hospital

356
00:18:48,280 --> 00:18:49,920
was to learn about interventions
from Zheng Ren.

357
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:50,730
After all,

358
00:18:51,130 --> 00:18:52,730
urology also needs interventions.

359
00:18:57,100 --> 00:18:58,530
Zheng Ren doesn't have that much energy.

360
00:18:59,350 --> 00:19:00,120
How many people can he teach?

361
00:19:01,110 --> 00:19:01,970
You or her?

362
00:19:03,310 --> 00:19:04,840
So this is what you trying to say.

363
00:19:05,240 --> 00:19:06,360
I'm your nephew.

364
00:19:06,630 --> 00:19:07,970
A real nephew

365
00:19:08,030 --> 00:19:08,970
who doesn't make money for the hospital?

366
00:19:10,520 --> 00:19:11,290
When do you plan to go

367
00:19:11,390 --> 00:19:12,210
on the operating table?

368
00:19:31,760 --> 00:19:32,680
Do you really have a way

369
00:19:32,870 --> 00:19:33,880
to get him back on his feet?

370
00:19:35,070 --> 00:19:36,010
Those who have seen the stars

371
00:19:36,920 --> 00:19:37,920
can't get away from them.

372
00:19:48,480 --> 00:19:49,680
Killing three birds with one stone.

373
00:19:52,630 --> 00:19:54,160
What's going to happen?

374
00:19:56,550 --> 00:19:57,250
I'm looking forward to it.

375
00:20:13,260 --> 00:20:14,330
60 points.

376
00:20:15,310 --> 00:20:15,770
No.

377
00:20:16,190 --> 00:20:17,120
70 at the most.

378
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,490
Much worse than me.

379
00:20:29,340 --> 00:20:31,940
[Emergency Office]

380
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:35,080
Congratulations on getting off work.

381
00:20:35,630 --> 00:20:36,830
In honor of the brothers'

382
00:20:36,830 --> 00:20:37,730
successful surgery,

383
00:20:37,790 --> 00:20:39,120
it's time for the monthly fellowship

384
00:20:39,130 --> 00:20:40,570
between the hospitals again.

385
00:20:40,600 --> 00:20:42,530
I, the single, have to take my chances.

386
00:20:42,870 --> 00:20:43,640
Unlike you two

387
00:20:43,720 --> 00:20:44,600
who have network addiction.

388
00:20:44,920 --> 00:20:45,680
Go for it!

389
00:20:47,920 --> 00:20:48,530
Yun.

390
00:20:48,630 --> 00:20:50,250
I have something to do. I'm not going.

391
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:51,530
See you.

392
00:20:51,760 --> 00:20:52,920
Yue, let's go.

393
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:54,010
OK.

394
00:20:54,960 --> 00:20:55,490
You're going too?

395
00:20:55,920 --> 00:20:56,400
Yes.

396
00:20:57,550 --> 00:20:58,250
Are you ready?

397
00:20:59,040 --> 00:20:59,730
Let's go.

398
00:20:59,790 --> 00:21:00,640
You're going too?

399
00:21:02,240 --> 00:21:03,120
Why can't I go?

400
00:21:04,310 --> 00:21:05,290
Really?

401
00:21:05,360 --> 00:21:06,840
Zheng, you're going too?

402
00:21:06,880 --> 00:21:07,960
Oh, no.

403
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:09,290
Everyone in the field now knows

404
00:21:09,350 --> 00:21:09,840
that Haicheng Hospital

405
00:21:09,920 --> 00:21:11,050
has an interventional genius,

406
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:11,920
a cancer survivor.

407
00:21:12,590 --> 00:21:13,160
If you go,

408
00:21:13,390 --> 00:21:14,210
no one will pay attention to me.

409
00:21:14,720 --> 00:21:15,330
I'm going.

410
00:21:15,870 --> 00:21:16,400
Yun,

411
00:21:16,460 --> 00:21:17,330
- you just said...
- Shut up.

412
00:21:17,350 --> 00:21:18,010
I'm backing out.

413
00:21:18,550 --> 00:21:19,330
I'll go change.

414
00:21:19,480 --> 00:21:20,050
Wait for me.

415
00:21:23,070 --> 00:21:24,160
- You're all going?
- Let's go.

416
00:21:24,440 --> 00:21:25,640
No one will notice me.

417
00:21:36,720 --> 00:21:37,970
Be careful.

418
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:48,120
Here?

419
00:21:48,280 --> 00:21:49,530
Good choice.

420
00:22:00,350 --> 00:22:00,880
Yue.

421
00:22:02,030 --> 00:22:03,080
Which boy do you like?

422
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:05,030
Let me know
if you're too embarrassed to tell him.

423
00:22:05,030 --> 00:22:06,160
I'll help you.

424
00:22:06,310 --> 00:22:07,770
I'm here for a drink.

425
00:22:07,790 --> 00:22:08,250
Do you want it?

426
00:22:08,280 --> 00:22:09,210
No.

427
00:22:09,680 --> 00:22:11,210
Then shut up.

428
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:12,680
No wonder

429
00:22:12,680 --> 00:22:13,600
you always fail.

430
00:22:15,630 --> 00:22:16,640
That's not true, Yun.

431
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:18,010
Every time Yue comes,

432
00:22:18,030 --> 00:22:19,680
many boys ask for her phone numbers.

433
00:22:19,830 --> 00:22:20,720
Really?

434
00:22:21,160 --> 00:22:22,440
Yue is the girl who receives

435
00:22:22,440 --> 00:22:23,730
the most flowers at Haicheng Hospital.

436
00:22:25,590 --> 00:22:27,530
They must be from patients' families

437
00:22:28,110 --> 00:22:29,770
who want to say thanks.

438
00:22:29,870 --> 00:22:30,600
You know nothing.

439
00:22:42,830 --> 00:22:43,490
500.

440
00:22:43,790 --> 00:22:45,070
It's not a good idea

441
00:22:45,070 --> 00:22:45,920
to study in this place.

442
00:22:47,060 --> 00:22:47,870
[3D Printing
Helps Separate Siamese Twins]

443
00:22:47,870 --> 00:22:48,840
It's not.

444
00:22:50,390 --> 00:22:51,250
Too noisy.

445
00:22:52,350 --> 00:22:53,870
Stop it. Let's go.

446
00:22:53,870 --> 00:22:54,680
Come and dance with me.

447
00:22:55,520 --> 00:22:56,490
Do you think I can dance?

448
00:22:56,720 --> 00:22:57,480
I can teach you.

449
00:22:57,480 --> 00:22:58,050
Come on.

450
00:22:58,790 --> 00:22:59,640
Stop it. Give it to me now.

451
00:23:00,070 --> 00:23:00,840
No.

452
00:23:00,870 --> 00:23:01,680
I'll give it to you when you can dance.

453
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:02,400
Give it to me now.

454
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:03,250
You've taught me so much,

455
00:23:03,280 --> 00:23:04,010
I should teach you something too.

456
00:23:04,480 --> 00:23:05,080
Sorry.

457
00:23:08,160 --> 00:23:08,970
It's you.

458
00:23:12,790 --> 00:23:13,600
Who called her here?

459
00:23:23,790 --> 00:23:24,440
Whammy.

460
00:23:25,070 --> 00:23:25,840
Su Yun.

461
00:23:26,630 --> 00:23:28,250
Graduated from a prestigious
medical university.

462
00:23:28,440 --> 00:23:29,010
Published a paper in The Lancet

463
00:23:29,070 --> 00:23:30,570
at the age of 21.

464
00:23:30,680 --> 00:23:31,770
After you

465
00:23:31,790 --> 00:23:33,110
did a heart transplant

466
00:23:33,110 --> 00:23:34,400
with autologous stem cells in mice,

467
00:23:34,480 --> 00:23:36,080
you became famous for a while.

468
00:23:41,520 --> 00:23:42,810
Then, because of the accident
of your teacher,

469
00:23:42,870 --> 00:23:43,920
Professor Wu,

470
00:23:44,070 --> 00:23:45,440
you were devastated.

471
00:23:45,680 --> 00:23:47,290
You returned to Haicheng Hospital
against all advice.

472
00:23:47,520 --> 00:23:48,570
You decided to stop doing surgeries

473
00:23:48,630 --> 00:23:50,120
and laze away in the Emergency Clinic.

474
00:23:51,310 --> 00:23:52,160
You were arrogant

475
00:23:52,280 --> 00:23:53,810
and thought you
were still the best in the world

476
00:23:53,960 --> 00:23:55,120
until you met Zheng Ren.

477
00:23:55,390 --> 00:23:56,880
Realizing that you couldn't surpass him,

478
00:23:56,960 --> 00:23:59,290
you became his shadow.

479
00:24:00,350 --> 00:24:01,530
Does it have anything to do with you?

480
00:24:08,630 --> 00:24:09,250
Anything else?

481
00:24:10,590 --> 00:24:11,360
I heard

482
00:24:11,390 --> 00:24:12,160
you've got PTSD

483
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:13,250
and can't operate anymore.

484
00:24:13,280 --> 00:24:14,050
With your condition,

485
00:24:14,070 --> 00:24:15,490
how dare you laugh
at my hands-on skills?

486
00:24:15,920 --> 00:24:17,530
I don't just laugh
at your hands-on skills.

487
00:24:17,920 --> 00:24:19,400
You're much worse

488
00:24:19,760 --> 00:24:20,680
at basic knowledge and experience.

489
00:24:25,920 --> 00:24:26,360
Let's do it?

490
00:24:26,390 --> 00:24:27,010
Sure.

491
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:27,770
No.

492
00:24:29,960 --> 00:24:30,570
Mr. Lin.

493
00:24:31,350 --> 00:24:32,210
I won't allow it.

494
00:24:34,310 --> 00:24:35,160
Do what?

495
00:24:40,240 --> 00:24:41,290
I shouldn't have agreed to you

496
00:24:41,290 --> 00:24:42,250
going to America in the first place.

497
00:24:42,870 --> 00:24:44,290
Look what you've become.

498
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:45,770
Degenerate.

499
00:24:49,310 --> 00:24:49,880
Starting tomorrow,

500
00:24:49,920 --> 00:24:50,810
let's face off.

501
00:24:51,030 --> 00:24:51,920
Competing on the reception rate
and cure rate.

502
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:52,730
For one month.

503
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:53,730
If you lose,

504
00:24:53,830 --> 00:24:55,530
I'll participate
in all Zheng Ren's surgeries from now on.

505
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:58,010
If you lose,

506
00:24:58,390 --> 00:24:59,050
go back to Man'ou.

507
00:24:59,070 --> 00:24:59,520
OK.

508
00:24:59,520 --> 00:25:00,810
Come on. Who cares?

509
00:25:03,280 --> 00:25:04,880
This is what we're going to do.

510
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:11,840
Your mom told me to ask you

511
00:25:12,630 --> 00:25:13,600
when you're coming home for dinner.

512
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:15,840
When I become vice president,

513
00:25:15,870 --> 00:25:17,250
I'll be home for the celebration dinner.

514
00:25:29,440 --> 00:25:30,010
Zheng.

515
00:25:30,680 --> 00:25:31,600
Don't you stop them?

516
00:25:33,790 --> 00:25:34,330
That's good.

517
00:25:35,350 --> 00:25:36,250
But Zheng...

518
00:25:36,310 --> 00:25:37,440
I think it's good too.

519
00:25:37,720 --> 00:25:38,210
What?

520
00:25:38,390 --> 00:25:38,790
Yue.

521
00:25:38,790 --> 00:25:40,400
Why are you also talking
like you don't care?

522
00:25:40,760 --> 00:25:41,400
I'm going home.

523
00:25:41,960 --> 00:25:42,570
Let's go together.

524
00:25:42,760 --> 00:25:43,840
Wait.

525
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:45,490
The fellowship has just begun.

526
00:25:45,870 --> 00:25:47,080
I've already seen what I want to see.

527
00:25:49,420 --> 00:25:50,040
But...

528
00:25:53,280 --> 00:25:54,570
Who's paying?

529
00:26:00,040 --> 00:26:00,810
See you.

530
00:26:01,080 --> 00:26:01,470
Bye.

531
00:26:01,470 --> 00:26:02,120
Bye.

532
00:26:09,720 --> 00:26:10,730
Hey, Yiren.

533
00:26:10,790 --> 00:26:11,530
How's it going?

534
00:26:11,590 --> 00:26:12,290
Did the plan go well?

535
00:26:13,030 --> 00:26:13,810
It all depends

536
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:15,160
on their final showdown.

537
00:26:15,240 --> 00:26:15,840
To be honest,

538
00:26:15,960 --> 00:26:16,840
when you first

539
00:26:16,920 --> 00:26:17,810
told me about this plan,

540
00:26:18,110 --> 00:26:19,570
I thought you came up with it.

541
00:26:19,820 --> 00:26:20,820
But I never expected it

542
00:26:20,820 --> 00:26:21,910
to be Zheng Ren.

543
00:26:25,580 --> 00:26:26,580
You want to find out from me

544
00:26:26,690 --> 00:26:28,230
which doctors are suitable

545
00:26:28,340 --> 00:26:29,740
to join the Siamese Surgery team?

546
00:26:31,140 --> 00:26:32,630
Don't you know the level

547
00:26:32,970 --> 00:26:34,020
of these doctors?

548
00:26:34,770 --> 00:26:36,340
You can tell by watching a surgery.

549
00:26:36,900 --> 00:26:37,740
Surgery can only show

550
00:26:37,740 --> 00:26:38,820
a doctor's skill level,

551
00:26:39,580 --> 00:26:40,630
but as a companion,

552
00:26:41,210 --> 00:26:42,230
they need something more.

553
00:26:44,010 --> 00:26:44,630
That's true.

554
00:26:46,420 --> 00:26:47,910
Then let's see their other side.

555
00:26:48,620 --> 00:26:49,740
Outside the hospital.

556
00:26:57,730 --> 00:26:59,470
I think they're all starting to change.

557
00:27:02,250 --> 00:27:03,110
I need to go.

558
00:27:03,620 --> 00:27:04,190
See you.

559
00:27:23,010 --> 00:27:23,580
Dad.

560
00:27:23,970 --> 00:27:25,360
What's this cabinet for?

561
00:27:26,210 --> 00:27:26,980
For instruments.

562
00:27:27,530 --> 00:27:29,180
For every successful surgery
you perform,

563
00:27:29,490 --> 00:27:30,470
I'll give you

564
00:27:30,530 --> 00:27:31,910
the latest customized instrument,

565
00:27:32,580 --> 00:27:33,580
but you have to promise me

566
00:27:34,290 --> 00:27:35,260
that after it's filled,

567
00:27:36,380 --> 00:27:37,950
you'll quit and come back home.

568
00:27:40,770 --> 00:27:41,950
You only invited Su Yun

569
00:27:42,180 --> 00:27:43,260
but not me.

570
00:27:43,820 --> 00:27:44,860
Is it because I'm not qualified

571
00:27:44,860 --> 00:27:45,870
to join your team?

572
00:27:58,700 --> 00:28:02,180
[Haicheng Hospital]

573
00:28:02,180 --> 00:28:04,420
[Urology]

574
00:28:10,530 --> 00:28:11,020
Come in.

575
00:28:11,900 --> 00:28:12,950
Do I have any surgeries today?

576
00:28:13,250 --> 00:28:14,390
Not yet.

577
00:28:14,490 --> 00:28:15,870
But there's a medical record

578
00:28:15,930 --> 00:28:16,580
in the gastroenterology department.

579
00:28:16,820 --> 00:28:17,740
They'd like you to take a look at it.

580
00:28:18,340 --> 00:28:19,970
[Medical records]

581
00:28:19,970 --> 00:28:20,580
What's the patient's problem?

582
00:28:21,580 --> 00:28:22,740
My wife has had diarrhea

583
00:28:23,250 --> 00:28:24,870
for almost five years.

584
00:28:25,060 --> 00:28:26,860
The patient
has had diarrhea for five years.

